Moving in is an experience that can stand alone in disorder without the added complication of finding a large dog sitting in the garden, waiting. Just waiting. Waiting like a collective character of all who have ever sought to belong somewhere. And the newly arrived family feels a responsibility to determine what he is waiting for.
